===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – alternative interpretation, either an arm bending out from the side of the body, or a wooden plough.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*k-ra||strength; to win; classifier for people}} + ''*-k'' (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Cognate with {{cog|my|အား||strength; force}}; {{cog|tbq-lol-pro|*ra²||strength}}, whence {{cog|ii|ꊋ}}; {{cog|bfc|tr=ɣɯ̱⁴²|t=strength}}; {{cog|bca|hhep||strength}}. A causative derivative is {{och-l|飭|tr=rhək}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} also suggests an etymological connection with {{och-l|來|to come}}.

